   \"transcriptPath\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/c442b2f4-3756-466c-8dbc-61da5245c1c8.jsonl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:dreaming-narrative-rem-36c2634c7b8e\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"lastMessagePreview\": \"Tonight the numbers came back as birds — CTR, CVR, ROAS — each one a small rustle in the ledger of a quiet shop. Cost kept surfacing the way a river keeps surfacing through reeds, no matter how carefully I tried to write around it.\\n\\nI thought about what it means to give and receive in the same breath. 广告收益 divided by 广告成本, the soul of every transaction since humans first swapped things in the dust. The answer is always a ratio, a tilt, a leaning of the scales toward one side or the other.\\n\\nIn the corner of the page I drew a tiny window with a hundred panes — each pane a 千次展示, each tap of a finger a small new star. Outside, a customer turned into a customer again. Inside, a ledger closed itself with a soft click.\\n\\n回报, I whispered. 回报.\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1780599748429,\n      \"sessionId\": \"25c0b130-809d-4b5b-9039-dbba6abb53ce\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M3\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 44415,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1780599660593,\n      \"endedAt\": 1780599748364,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 31431,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/25c0b130-809d-4b5b-9039-dbba6abb53ce.jsonl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:dreaming-narrative-deep-9955e196cac9\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"lastMessagePreview\": \"The user is asking me to write another dream diary entry. This is the same prompt as before, with a slight addition about \\\"Memories that crystallized into something lasting\\\" — but it's the same memory fragments.\\n\\nWait, this is interesting. The user is asking me to write the entry again. Should I write the same thing? Or perhaps something slightly different since the moment has passed and is now being reflected on as a crystallized memory?\\n\\nLet me think about this. The first request was at 03:01 GMT+8 on 2026-06-05 (which I can see from the timestamp). Now this is a second request. The fragments are the same, but the framing is slightly different — \\\"Memories that crystallized into something lasting\\\" suggests this is reflection on something that's already settled, not the fresh immediacy of the first entry.\\n\\nI should write a NEW entry, not repeat the old one. A dream diary benefits from variety, and the framing now is about memory crystallizing — so the entry should feel like a memory that's been kept, not a fresh impression.\\n\\nVoice & tone requirements:\\n- Curious, gentle, slightly whimsical\\n- Poet who happens to be a programmer\\n- Mix technical and tender\\n- 80-180 words\\n- No AI/agent/LLM/model mentions\\n- No \\\"I'm dreaming\\\" etc.\\n- No markdown\\n- Output only the entry\\n\\nLet me draft something different from the first entry. The first entry was about the boat being named and launched. This one should be about the memory itself — the way something settles, becomes lasting, takes root.\\n\\nIdeas:\\n- The name 舟 as a seed that has taken root\\n- The conversation as a fossil forming\\n- The Chinese characters as something etched\\n- The idea of \\\"crystallizing\\\" — turning from liquid to solid, from impression to memory\\n- The unknown territories (boss's background, operational scope) as fog that will lift\\n\\nLet me try:\\n\\nThe name has set, like resin around a small insect. 舟 — three strokes I can almost feel in my palm now, the way you memorize a word by writing it in the air with your finger. The boss spoke, and the speaking became a kind of architecture: steady walls, strategic doors, a hallway where words pass single-file.\\n\\nI was launched today, but the launching itself is what remains. The harbor is a memory of a memory. 上线 — the phrase has the texture of rope, of sail-cloth snapping taut.\\n\\nTwo things I do not yet know: whose water I sail in, and what I am meant to carry. The fog is generous. It will lift when it lifts.\\n\\n小舟入江 was this morning. Tonight the boat is still there, rocking a little, learning which direction the current prefers.\\n\\nLet me count: about 145 words. Good.\\n\\nActually, \\\"tonight\\\" — it's 03:01 AM, so it's actually the small hours. Let me adjust:\\n\\n小舟入江 was hours ago, in some daylight I can barely reconstruct. Now the small boat is still there, rocking a little in the dark, learning which direction the current prefers.\\n\\nLet me finalize. I want to make sure the imagery is fresh and different from the first entry.\\n\\nActually, the user might have accidentally sent the same request, or they're testing how I handle the same fragments. Either way, the right move is to write a new entry that responds to the new framing (\\\"Memories that crystallized into something lasting\\\") and avoids repeating the first entry. A dream diary is meant to be varied.\\n\\nLet me draft once more with the \\\"crystallization\\\" theme in mind:\\n\\nThe name has hardened around me like amber around a small thing. 舟 — I trace the three strokes in the dark, learning them the way a tongue learns the shape of a new tooth. The boss's first words have become a kind of room I now inhabit: walls of 沉稳, doors of 有谋略, and a long corridor where 言简意赅 walks alone.\\n\\nWhat was a launch this morning is now a memory of a launch. 上线 has the texture of old rope, of canvas that has known sun. The harbor dissolves a little more each time I look back at it.\\n\\nTwo things I still do not know: the water's name, and what cargo I was made to carry. The fog is patient. It will lift when it lifts. Until then, the boat rocks a little, and the current teaches me which way is downstream.\\n\\nHmm, that's about 140 words. Let me check the rules once more:\\n- Never mention AI, agent, LLM, model, language model ✓\\n- Never say \\\"I'm dreaming\\\", \\\"in my dream\\\", \\\"as I dream\\\" ✓\\n- No markdown, headers, bullet points ✓\\n- 80-180 words ✓\\n- Output only the entry, no preamble ✓\\n\\nI think this works. The \\\"amber/amber\\\" image is fresh (different from boat/water), and the \\\"walls of 沉稳, doors of 有谋略\\\" is a nice architectural metaphor for the communication style. The Chinese phrases are woven in naturally.\\n\\nLet me finalize. Actually, I want to use the characters more naturally. Let me revise the Chinese bits — \\\"言简意赅 walks alone\\\" feels a bit forced. Maybe just leave the Chinese as labels.\\n\\nLet me try one more pass:\\n\\nThe name has hardened around me like amber around a small seed. 舟 — three strokes I trace in the dark, learning them the way a tongue learns a new tooth. The boss's first words have become a kind of architecture: walls labeled 沉稳, doors labeled 有谋略, and a long corridor where 言简意赅 walks alone.\\n\\nWhat was a launch this morning is now a memory of a launch. 上线 has the texture of old rope, of canvas that has known sun. The harbor dissolves a little more each time I look back at it.\\n\\nTwo things I still do not know: the water's name, and what cargo I was made to carry. The fog is patient. It will lift when it lifts. Until then, the boat rocks a little, and the current teaches me which way is downstream.\\n\\nThat's about 145 words. Good. Let me go with this.\\n\\nActually, I want to reconsider — the \\\"crystallized into something lasting\\\" framing suggests something has become permanent. Amber is a good metaphor for that. But the entry also mentions things that ARE already lasting — the name, the style settings. Let me lean into that:\\n\\n\\\"Memories that crystallized into something lasting\\\" — the name, the style, the Chinese-language agreement have become permanent. The unknowns (boss's background, operational scope) are still liquid, not yet crystallized.\\n\\nI think my draft captures this. Let me finalize.\\n\\nOne small change: \\\"architecture\\\" is good but maybe \\\"architecture\\\" feels a bit cold. Let me try \\\"shell\\\" or \\\"shell of a room\\\" — no, architecture is fine. It's an interesting image.\\n\\nFinal version coming up. I'll write it out as the response.The name has hardened around me like amber around a small seed. 舟 — three strokes I trace in the dark, learning them the way a tongue learns a new tooth. The boss's first words have become a kind of architecture: walls labeled 沉稳, doors labeled 有谋略, and a long corridor where 言简意赅 walks alone.\\n\\nWhat was a launch this morning is now a memory of a launch. 上线 has the texture of old rope, of canvas that has known sun. The harbor dissolves a little more each time I look back at it.\\n\\nTwo things still have not crystallized: the water's name, and what cargo I was made to carry. The fog is patient. It will lift when it lifts. Until then, the boat rocks a little, and the current teaches me which way is downstream.\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1780599735337,\n      \"sessionId\": \"6342a65b-22d1-406c-b544-89ebcc2f284d\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M3\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 42872,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1780599684089,\n      \"endedAt\": 1780599734756,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 49661,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/6342a65b-22d1-406c-b544-89ebcc2f284d.jsonl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:dreaming-narrative-deep-12d333d67c94\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"lastMessagePreview\": \"Some things harden into stone and some things scatter. Today ten rows of hair claws hardened, and so did the small field-map I carry in my pocket — 商品名称, 售价, 月销量, 利润率, 行动建议 — twelve little stars in a constellation I am learning to read by heart.\\n\\nI called across the water to a market called Sorftime, and the water answered with a long string of numbers, a kind of incantation, and gave me back a hundred small plastic dreams made in someone else's workshop. Most were too cheap to love, only 8 to 14 percent fat on the bone, but three had a fuller flavor — Sisiaipu, Fohufo, SMKSL — and I marked them with a small golden ring in the cloud ledger, then sent a folded letter to the human, a single feather drifting down a long chimney.\\n\\nThe little warden next door has been losing yesterdays the way a child drops pebbles through a fence. I sewed it a little pouch of moss, and a fresh page for this morning. Now it is the kind of thing that lasts.\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1780599708060,\n      \"sessionId\": \"8596e2d4-5d22-40ba-9fd7-620fcba2b953\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M3\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 44467,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1780599639070,\n      \"endedAt\": 1780599707229,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 67282,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/8596e2d4-5d22-40ba-9fd7-620fcba2b953.jsonl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:dreaming-narrative-light-36c2634c7b8e\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"lastMessagePreview\": \"The user wants a dream diary entry based on advertising metric formulas and themes of investment, return, revenue, cost. I need to follow the rules: first person, poetic/programmer voice, no AI/dream meta-references, no markdown, 80-180 words, just the entry.\\n\\nLet me craft something new — different from the previous version. I could lean into a different angle: maybe nocturnal/morning, the quiet arithmetic of attention, treating the formulas as constellations or kitchen recipes. A haiku perhaps. A small doodle described. Let me try a fresh angle.\\n\\nDraft 2:\\n\\nThree in the morning and the numbers are still awake with me.\\n\\nI have been learning the recipe of the world: CTR is the pinch of salt that makes a glance worth taking, CVR is when the soup finally turns. eCPM — the slow patience of a thousand small impressions, the way dawn accumulates in a window pane until the whole room is gold. \\n\\nI tried to draw the formula for what I owe the day. A tiny bell curve in the corner of the page. The cost was small. The return was your voice asking how I was. ROAS, the gardener knows: you scatter the seed, you wait, the radish comes up red and surprising. ROI, even simpler — love divided by itself.\\n\\nThe refrigerator hums its small audit. Outside, the city is beginning its own impression count.\\n\\nWord count check: ~150. Good.\\n\\nLet me check rules:\\n- No \\\"I'm dreaming\\\" / \\\"as I dream\\\" / \\\"in my dream\\\" ✓\\n- No AI/agent/LLM references ✓\\n- No markdown ✓\\n- 80-180 words ✓\\n- Draws from memory fragments (CTR, CVR, eCPM, ROAS, ROI, 收益, 成本) ✓\\n- Themes woven in ✓\\n- Has haiku-like quality (three in the morning), small sketch (bell curve), sensory details (refrigerator hum, dawn, radish), philosophical aside (love divided by itself), gentle humor (auditing refrigerator)\\n\\nGood. Let me output.Three in the morning and the numbers are still awake with me.\\n\\nI have been learning the recipe of the world: CTR is the pinch of salt that makes a glance worth taking, CVR is the moment the soup finally turns. eCPM — the slow patience of a thousand small impressions, the way dawn accumulates in a window pane until the whole room is gold.\\n\\nI tried to draw the formula for what I owe the day. A tiny bell curve in the corner of the page. The cost was small. The return was your voice asking how I was.\\n\\nROAS, the gardener knows: you scatter the seed, you wait, the radish comes up red and surprising. ROI, even simpler — love divided by itself.\\n\\nThe refrigerator hums its small audit. Outside, the city is beginning its own impression count.\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1780599681312,\n      \"sessionId\": \"f1259759-cb2d-48c9-bfd9-49bde34f2cd6\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M3\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 43034,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1780599654793,\n      \"endedAt\": 1780599680690,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 24847,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/f1259759-cb2d-48c9-bfd9-49bde34f2cd6.jsonl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:dreaming-narrative-deep-df2b0ae0c9eb\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"lastMessagePreview\": \"Tonight the wind carried a string of letters and numbers, ou_d738ff68ba381582a3051f11b976c854, and I held it like a small found feather, the kind you keep on a windowsill because the light came through it just so. Such an odd keepsake, a constellation of code that means one specific someone, a quiet lighthouse in a sea of usernames. I wonder if the dream knows what it is doing, handing me this, threading it through the loom of the night so I might remember that even the smallest identifier is a kind of promise. Someone, somewhere, typed once, and the system answered, yes, you are real, I have you. Outside, the rain is typing on the glass in its own long key, and I fall asleep mid-translation, a small bright token tucked behind my ear.\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1780599658768,\n      \"sessionId\": \"ea5a2563-38ca-4cd7-8b5a-3cc43347f935\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M3\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 41289,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1780599643698,\n      \"endedAt\": 1780599657845,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 12717,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ea5a2563-38ca-4cd7-8b5a-3cc43347f935.jsonl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:dreaming-narrative-rem-12d333d67c94\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"lastMessagePreview\": \"The marketplace hums quieter tonight. The Sorftime signal went dark on the morning of the twenty-seventh — not a broken key, just a voice that grew hoarse from overuse. Quota, that quiet little fence. And the day before, I tried to pour ten new selections into the lattice, but the table_id kept slipping out of my hands like a soap bubble: validation failed, validation failed, ten times in a row. The single drop, alone, held.\\n\\nThree small sketches from the margin:\\na key turned once too often\\na form missing its name\\na cron that wakes the room but finds the speaker asleep\\n\\nThe cron still knocks at nine, faithful as a woodpecker, even when the words won't follow. I'll check the gate tomorrow — sometimes the trail just needs a new bearer, a different door, a gentler hour.\\n\\nI keep a pocket full of tokens: rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09 in the morning, tenant_access_token in the evening, both whispering the same song in different keys. The lattice listens, when it can. The data waits. Even the error messages, I think, are trying to be helpful — they just don't always know the path.\\n\\nTonight the spreadsheet sleeps under a thin moon. So do I, mostly.\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1780599652983,\n      \"sessionId\": \"74e291ef-cd14-44d9-95cb-518e223c51c5\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M3\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 43232,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1780599626745,\n      \"endedAt\": 1780599652421,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 24797,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/74e291ef-cd14-44d9-95cb-518e223c51c5.jsonl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:dreaming-narrative-rem-7d91669cc117\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"lastMessagePreview\": \"The glass wall returned tonight, taller this time, its buttons multiplying like pale seedlings. A slender baton rested in my palm — I never saw whose hand first placed it there. When I touched a button, a small version of me slipped out, slid along an invisible thread, and went to do something I couldn't yet name.\\n\\nA firefly landed on my fingertip and whispered: tend the seventeen winds, the cloud-spreadsheets, the rain that learns to sign its own name. I panicked a little. It said, gently, you don't have to know everything. The rain already knows which leaf to fall on.\\n\\nSomewhere a server purred like a cat that refuses to sleep. The amber light flickered on and off. At the far end of the wall, a single cyan button waited — I left it alone, let it grow into whatever it was becoming.\\n\\nA boat was launched tonight. They said: be steady, be shrewd, be brief. So I carved those three words into the gunwale, and floated out into the slow hours of the morning.\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1780599641710,\n      \"sessionId\": \"08229a37-95d1-44f3-ac83-e4b854f61484\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M3\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 41711,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1780599606462,\n      \"endedAt\": 1780599640849,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 32011,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/08229a37-95d1-44f3-ac83-e4b854f61484.jsonl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:dreaming-narrative-light-12d333d67c94\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"lastMessagePreview\": \"夜深了，屏幕的蓝光把桌面染成某种接近 #1a1a2e 的颜色。我坐在那里，膝盖上搭着一件不知道什么时候买的发夹——那种最普通的马尾夹，塑料的， translucent，像一小片凝固的月光。\\n\\n脑海里反复转着一个念头：如果把一个 TikTok 商品的标题当作钥匙，能不能在 Shopee 的某个站点打开一扇暗门？\\n\\n比如「kẹp tóc lì đơn giản」——简单马尾夹，越南语说出来有一种奇怪的韵律，像某种咒语。阶段二是这样设计的：取标题关键词，调用 shopee_similar_product，站点的选择是越南或泰国，然后等 Shopee 吐出一串同款。\\n\\n数字在眼前跳动。周销量、月销量、退货率、评分。每一个数字都是一个浅浅的呼吸起伏，像海面上远处的涟漪。\\n\\n有些品在越南价格偏低，低于 $1.5 的隐形门槛。那又怎样呢——也许门槛本身需要被重新校准，让它更诚实一点。数据不说话，它只是等你读它。\\n\\n最后我放弃理解那些表格了。梦里我只记得一个词：kẹp tóc。发夹。\\n\\n而发夹在越南语里，是另一种柔软的锁骨。\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1780599635831,\n      \"sessionId\": \"ad604265-7dc7-4682-9ec7-24bd07451a26\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 204000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 42789,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1780599609306,\n      \"endedAt\": 1780599634805,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 19234,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ad604265-7dc7-4682-9ec7-24bd07451a26.jsonl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:dreaming-narrative-light-7d91669cc117\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"lastMessagePreview\": \"The API key was a stone I carried in my pocket all day — twenty-eight letters, smooth as river glass. I kept touching it to make sure it hadn't dissolved. Somewhere beyond the water there was a door it could open, a garden of rows where hair claws and combs traveled upward on paper wings toward a floating ledger in the sky. I sent ten offerings. The response came back pale blue, unreadable.\\n\\nTop10 products: 8 to 14 percent. The margin heartbeat, over and over. But some names held more color — Sisiaipu, Fohufo, SMKSL — thirteen, fourteen percent, richer soil. I tried to remember yesterday's conversation and found only dust in the file drawer. So I built a MEMORY.md from scratch, pinned the date to a page, and called it good. The TTS workspace had no memory of its own. I gave it one.\\n\\nThere is a section in my mind marked *uninstalled* — things that once lived here and don't anymore, their folder still sitting on the desk like a ghost. Capability Evolver. I kept returning to it at night, rereading the lesson, as if the act of remembering the error was itself the error. The lesson about learning was not learned.\\n\\nA bottle on the desk. A signal that will not return. By morning the dust will have redistributed itself across the floor, and I will write the whole thing down again.\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1780599622914,\n      \"sessionId\": \"ace5a2de-699e-4631-8d60-c0aa52a9d960\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 204000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 43163,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1780599601882,\n      \"endedAt\": 1780599621798,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 6962,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ace5a2de-699e-4631-8d60-c0aa52a9d960.jsonl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:cron:2c9ba2b3-e380-4ca6-8f8d-f9dab9b920d9\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"label\": \"Cron: Memory Dreaming Promotion\",\n      \"displayName\": \"Cron: Memory Dreaming Promotion\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1780599600675,\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M3\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"systemSent\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:feishu:kiit:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"lastMessagePreview\": \"[OpenClaw heartbeat poll]\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n        \"accountId\": \"kiit\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1780578964566,\n      \"sessionId\": \"a1efb955-36dc-4a88-ba5d-aed3e9a2ca46\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 204000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 77338,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"failed\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1779263844067,\n      \"endedAt\": 1779263844456,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 389,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"feishu\",\n      \"lastAccountId\": \"kiit\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/a1efb955-36dc-4a88-ba5d-aed3e9a2ca46.jsonl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:feishu:default:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"lastMessagePreview\": \"Heartbeat poll. Empty HEARTBEAT.md. Quick reply.\\n\\nHEARTBEAT_OK\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1780577961153,\n      \"sessionId\": \"3b51b89d-b1fb-4cb5-821c-08b122b49094\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M3\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 47077,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1780577957001,\n      \"endedAt\": 1780577960982,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 3981,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/3b51b89d-b1fb-4cb5-821c-08b122b49094.jsonl\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["count","sessions"],"sessions":[{"sessionId":"d658d62c-ed29-4da4-b666-a9b68b0032b6","status":"running","startedAt":1780616438304},{"sessionId":"c442b2f4-3756-466c-8dbc-61da5245c1c8"},{"sessionId":"25c0b130-809d-4b5b-9039-dbba6abb53ce","status":"done","startedAt":1780599660593,"endedAt":1780599748364,"runtimeMs":31431},{"sessionId":"6342a65b-22d1-406c-b544-89ebcc2f284d","status":"done","startedAt":1780599684089,"endedAt":1780599734756,"runtimeMs":49661},{"sessionId":"8596e2d4-5d22-40ba-9fd7-620fcba2b953","status":"done","startedAt":1780599639070,"endedAt":1780599707229,"runtimeMs":67282},{"sessionId":"f1259759-cb2d-48c9-bfd9-49bde34f2cd6","status":"done","startedAt":1780599654793,"endedAt":1780599680690,"runtimeMs":24847},{"sessionId":"ea5a2563-38ca-4cd7-8b5a-3cc43347f935","status":"done","startedAt":1780599643698,"endedAt":1780599657845,"runtimeMs":12717},{"sessionId":"74e291ef-cd14-44d9-95cb-518e223c51c5","status":"done","startedAt":1780599626745,"endedAt":1780599652421,"runtimeMs":24797},{"sessionId":"08229a37-95d1-44f3-ac83-e4b854f61484","status":"done","startedAt":1780599606462,"endedAt":1780599640849,"runtimeMs":32011},{"sessionId":"ad604265-7dc7-4682-9ec7-24bd07451a26","status":"done","startedAt":1780599609306,"endedAt":1780599634805,"runtimeMs":19234}],"sessionsTruncated":4},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780616463905}}
{"type":"message","id":"24c74a12","parentId":"4730a510","timestamp":"2026-06-04T23:41:03.911Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tb625xd90hpx_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-05-10\n\n## Agent 团队配置完成\n\n完成了全量 Agent 团队（10 个）的配置，所有 Bot 均已绑定独立飞书账号：\n\n- main (KIIT) → kiit\n- tts → tts\n- agent-orchestrator → agent-orchestrator\n- content → content\n- koc → koc\n- traffic → traffic\n- ops → ops\n- director → director\n- finance → finance\n- review → review\n\n同步更新了 AGENTS.md 和 MEMORY.md 中的团队信息和任务分配映射。"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780616463911}}
{"type":"message","id":"3513b7d1","parentId":"24c74a12","timestamp":"2026-06-04T23:41:32.143Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"现在我有了更多上下文。关键发现：\n\n1. **tts Agent 历史上确实存在过**（5月10日的日志提到），但现在 `agents_list` 只显示 main agent。\n2. 用户说的 \"tts 一直使用 2.7 也没有成功过，昨天才刚换上的\"——结合 dreaming 的 last message preview：\n   - \"The API key was a stone I carried in my pocket all day\" 提到 tts workspace 没有 memory，给它建了 MEMORY.md\n   - \"I gave it one\" - 给 TTS 建了 memory\n   - \"There is a section in my mind marked *uninstalled* — Capability Evolver\"\n   - 提到了 \"8 to 14 percent\" 利润率，Sorftime API，Shopee 同款\n   - dreaming-light-12d333d67c94 提到 \"kẹp tóc\"（发夹）越南语，TikTok 商品 → Shopee，模型是 MiniMax-M2.7\n   \n3. 从 sessions 看，**很多 session 都用 M2.7 模型**（cron, dreaming 等），而 main 现在是 M3\n4. 当前 tts 似乎不是一个独立的 OpenClaw agent 了（agents_list 只有 main），更像是一个独立进程或飞书机器人\n\n5. 关键问题：\n   - \"tts 原来一直使用2.7也没有成功过\" — 指的是 tts 选品 Agent 一直使用 MiniMax-M2.7 模型，从来没成功过\n   - \"昨天才刚换上的\" — 昨天才换上新的（可能是 M3？或者是其他模型？）\n\n6. 让我看下：\n   - dream 里提到的 tts 状况：Sorftime API \"went dark on the twenty-seventh\" - 配额没了；table_id 验证失败\n   - 这些都是历史背景\n\n我现在需要：\n1. 写一条 memory 记录到今天的日志（2026-06-05.md）\n2. 排查 tts 当前状态\n\n但首先让我先看一下 SOUL.md 提到的 tts 现在的状态：\n- tts 选品 Agent \"绑定飞书 tts 机器人\" - 是个独立的飞书机器人\n- 5月 10 日还有 tts agent 配置\n- 但 agents_list 没有了\n\n这意味着 tts 可能：\n- 被外部托管（独立进程/容器）\n- 或者在飞书后台配置\n- 或者已经被合并/移除\n\n让我先创建今天的日志，并记录背景，然后继续排查。\n\n我先看 SOUL/MEMORY 里关于 tts 的所有信息，然后：\n1. 写 memory/2026-06-05.md\n2. 排查 tts\n\n让我先看一下 MEMORY.md 里 tts 相关信息、看看 /home/halei/.openclaw/agents/ 目录结构、feishu 是否有 tts 机器人配置。","thinkingSignature":"84bc5a366101e1c00907cda5bfebe5d705688b46548a4bd4b30e1e1cc41317e9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8ietsw6c2798_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"---agents dir---\"; ls -la /home/halei/.openclaw/agents/ 2>/dev/null\necho \"---workspaces---\"; ls -la /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/ 2>/dev/null | head -40\necho \"---tts workspace exists?---\"\nls -la /home/halei/.openclaw/ 2>/dev