{"type":"message","id":"90d09ec8","parentId":"e0cfc932","timestamp":"2026-06-05T00:32:56.438Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand. The main agent uses `MiniMax-M3` with the `minimax(49套餐)` provider (different from the `minimax` provider the tts agent uses). The tts agent only has `MiniMax-M2.7` in its models.json.\n\nThe user said \"昨天晚上还上的 3.0\" - meaning they changed it to M3 last night. But the models.json doesn't have M3. So the user likely modified the config.json `model` field to `\"MiniMax-M3\"` but:\n1. The models.json still only has M2.7 registered\n\n\n2. Since the model wasn't available in models.json, the change never actually took effect and the agent kept using M2.7\n\nThe solution is to update tts's models.json to register M3 following the main agent's pattern, using the same provider credentials from the existing minimax provider.\n","thinkingSignature":"d1beb5cc33600d5e9c75f4300ff8ddcc1199907970ec1140fb35c7bd2186c601"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pa912ueugmtd_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"  \"minimax(49套餐)\": {\n    \"baseUrl\": \"https://api.minimaxi.com/anthropic/v1\",\n    \"apiKey\": \"sk-cp-…s38c\",\n    \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n    \"models\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"MiniMax-M3\",\n        \"input\": [\n          \"text\",\n          \"image\"\n        ],\n        \"name\": \"MiniMax-M3\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n        \"input\": [\n          \"text\",\n          \"image\"\n        ],\n        \"name\": \"MiniMax M2.7\",\n        \"contextWindow\": 204000,\n        \"reasoning\": true\n      }\n    ]\n  }","oldText":"  \"minimax\": {\n    \"baseUrl\": \"https://api.minimaxi.com/anthropic/v1\",\n    \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n    \"authHeader\": true,\n    \"models\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n        \"name\": \"MiniMax M2.7\",\n        \"contextWindow\": 204000,\n        \"input\": [\