{"type":"message","id":"07e3669b","parentId":"15d76a2d","timestamp":"2026-06-05T00:33:28.399Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Config looks correct. Now I need to restart the tts agent so it picks up the new config. Let me use the gateway tool or the openclaw CLI to restart the tts agent specifically.\n\nActually, looking at the gateway tool - it seems to restart the whole gateway, not individual agents. Let me check if there's a way to restart just the tts agent.\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to trigger a new session for the tts agent, which will cause it to pick up the new config. But actually, I think openclaw agents load their config at startup, so we need to somehow restart the agent's runtime.\n \nI found the openclaw gateway restart command, but that restarts everything. Since there's no per-agent restart command documented, I'll try sending a message to the tts agent - if it's running, it'll receive it and the new session will load the updated config, or the gateway might handle restarting it automatically.\n","thinkingSignature":"15d778db95dc672bb1dffd9d0c25fad59fb05cf8786b48e82e71eb0f52b4fbe7"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n配置已改好，现在重启 tts agent 让新配置生效。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rktg4l6vss9a_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"restart","note":"tts agent config 更新完毕，models.json 加了 M3，config.json model 改为 MiniMax-M3，请重启 agent 使新配置生效"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4696,"output":268,"cacheRead":76881,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81845,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780619599021,"responseId":"06714c4f448b0a2b6c3c49f6b16fc9d2"}}
